comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
This is the NA-50, predecessor to the P-64, or NA-50A. There are many obvious differences, most notably in this photo, the rudder. The photo, if cleaned up, would also show a small triangular window below the forward fixed canopy. It was the only one of the 7 NA-50s to have this fitting.

Doug MacPhail
